text: The coat of arms of Guanajuato is the heraldic symbol representing the Mexican state of Guanajuato. The coat of arms shows an image of Santa Fe de la Granada, which symbolizes the triumph of the Catholic Monarchs over the Muslims. Holding the shield from the bottom are a shell and two laurel branches on a marble base.http://cedocvirtual.sectur.gob.mx/janium/Documentos/13215.pdf Boletín Trimestral de Destinos == References == :Category:North American coats of arms :Category:Guanajuato Guanajuato
